<!DOCTYPE html><html lang="en"><head><meta charSet="utf-8"/><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1"/><link rel="preload" href="/_next/static/media/051742360c26797e-s.p.0f97p8c3305p~.woff2" as="font" crossorigin="" type="font/woff2"/><link rel="preload" href="/_next/static/media/797e433ab948586e-s.p.09zddjkbdep5a.woff2" as="font" crossorigin="" type="font/woff2"/><link rel="preload" href="/_next/static/media/7ebf22b5a21034f8-s.p.10_7676vm7pyy.woff2" as="font" crossorigin="" type="font/woff2"/><link rel="preload" href="/_next/static/media/caa3a2e1cccd8315-s.p.09~u27dqhyhd6.woff2" as="font" crossorigin="" type="font/woff2"/><link rel="preload" href="/_next/static/media/e41d5df559864f9e-s.p.0gq7fw9.sy_5..woff2" as="font" crossorigin="" type="font/woff2"/><link rel="preload" as="image" imageSrcSet="/pagegains-logo-new.png"/><link rel="stylesheet" href="/_next/static/chunks/0u_qnwyw1l4uj.css" data-precedence="next"/><link rel="stylesheet" href="/_next/static/chunks/049yatv45ooot.css" data-precedence="next"/><meta name="next-size-adjust" content=""/><title>Free 111-Point Ecommerce CRO Checklist — Score Your Store | PageGains</title><meta name="description" content="Use our free interactive 111-point ecommerce CRO checklist to score your store&#x27;s conversion rate. Covers homepage, product pages, cart, checkout, mobile &amp; more. Takes ~10 minutes. No account needed."/><meta name="keywords" content="ecommerce CRO checklist,ecommerce conversion checklist,ecommerce conversion rate optimization checklist,shopify CRO checklist,ecommerce optimization checklist,conversion rate optimization,ecommerce audit checklist"/><link rel="canonical" href="/ecommerce-cro-checklist"/><meta property="og:title" content="Free 111-Point Ecommerce CRO Checklist — Score Your Store"/><meta property="og:description" content="Tick off what you&#x27;ve implemented across 111 proven conversion tactics. Get a live score, see your biggest gaps, and find out exactly what&#x27;s costing you sales."/><meta property="og:url" content="/ecommerce-cro-checklist"/><meta property="og:site_name" content="PageGains"/><meta property="og:image" content="/cro-checklist-preview.png"/><meta property="og:image:width" content="1200"/><meta property="og:image:height" content="630"/><meta property="og:image:alt" content="PageGains 111-Point Ecommerce CRO Checklist"/><meta property="og:type" content="website"/><meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image"/><meta name="twitter:title" content="Free 111-Point Ecommerce CRO Checklist — Score Your Store"/><meta name="twitter:description" content="Tick off what you&#x27;ve implemented across 111 proven conversion tactics. Get a live score, see your biggest gaps."/><meta name="twitter:image" content="/cro-checklist-preview.png"/><link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico?favicon.0-ehtld.olem8.ico" sizes="48x48" type="image/x-icon"/><link rel="icon" href="/favicon.png" type="image/png"/><link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/favicon.png"/></head><body class="geist_a71539c9-module__T19VSG__variable geist_mono_8d43a2aa-module__8Li5zG__variable jetbrains_mono_c765f1e1-module__TOcNWq__variable instrument_serif_90178cf-module__2pLAta__variable antialiased"><div hidden=""><!--$--><!--/$--></div><!--$!--><template data-dgst="BAILOUT_TO_CLIENT_SIDE_RENDERING"></template><!--/$--><div style="min-height:100vh;display:flex;flex-direction:column;background:#f6f4ef"><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"HowTo","name":"111-Point Ecommerce CRO Checklist: Score Your Store's Conversion Rate","description":"A complete, interactive ecommerce conversion rate optimization (CRO) checklist covering 12 key areas: homepage, product pages, cart, checkout, trust signals, mobile, search, email, page speed, analytics, copywriting, and post-purchase.","totalTime":"PT10M","tool":[{"@type":"HowToTool","name":"PageGains CRO Checklist"}],"supply":[{"@type":"HowToSupply","name":"Your ecommerce store URL"}],"step":[{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Homepage & First Impressions (12 checks)","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":1,"name":"Headline instantly answers: 'What do you sell, and why buy here?'","text":"If a new visitor can't understand what you sell in 3 seconds, they're gone. A vague headline is silently killing up to 20% of your traffic before they even scroll."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":2,"name":"Sub-headline names your target customer and key differentiator","text":"Without specificity, shoppers feel 'this isn't for me' and bounce. When your sub-headline names them directly, engagement deepens and click-through to product pages increases."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":3,"name":"Hero image shows your best-seller in real-life use","text":"Lifestyle imagery triggers emotional buying responses. Stores using contextual hero images see 28% higher engagement than those with plain white-background shots."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":4,"name":"Primary CTA above the fold uses action copy like 'Shop Best Sellers'","text":"Without a clear CTA above the fold, visitors who came ready to buy have nowhere to click. Vague CTAs like 'Learn More' lose shoppers who were already in buying mode."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":5,"name":"Homepage loads in under 3 seconds on mobile","text":"Every extra second of load time costs you 7% of conversions. On a store doing $10K/month, a 2-second delay means $1,400/month in lost sales."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":6,"name":"Trust badges visible above the fold: secure checkout, payment methods, guarantees","text":"53% of online shoppers say trust badges influence their buying decisions. Showing them early reduces the perceived risk of shopping with an unfamiliar brand."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":7,"name":"Navigation has 7 or fewer product categories with clear labels","text":"Too many options cause decision paralysis. Simple navigation helps shoppers find products faster, reducing drop-off between homepage and product pages."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":8,"name":"Product search bar is prominent with image/price autocomplete","text":"Shoppers who use site search convert 2–3x more often than browsers. Rich autocomplete with thumbnails and prices shortens the path to purchase."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":9,"name":"Social proof on homepage: total reviews, orders, or happy customers count","text":"Without social proof, new visitors have zero reason to trust you. Aggregate numbers ('50,000+ orders shipped') create a bandwagon effect that makes new visitors feel safe buying."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":10,"name":"Mobile menu opens instantly with product categories listed first","text":"On mobile, 70%+ of e-commerce traffic wants products — not 'About Us'. Prioritizing categories in the menu cuts clicks-to-product."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":11,"name":"Exit-intent popup offers a first-order incentive, not just 'subscribe'","text":"A targeted exit offer (10% off, free shipping) recovers 5–15% of abandoning visitors. Generic newsletter popups convert under 2%."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":12,"name":"Announcement bar highlights current promo or free shipping threshold","text":"A persistent, visible promo bar increases average order value by nudging shoppers toward the free shipping minimum — a proven AOV lever."}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Product Pages (14 checks)","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":1,"name":"Minimum 5 high-quality images: front, back, detail, scale, lifestyle","text":"If your product has fewer than 5 images, you're likely losing 30–50% of potential buyers. Images are the only thing standing between doubt and purchase."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":2,"name":"Zoom-on-hover or pinch-to-zoom works on desktop and mobile","text":"Letting shoppers inspect fabric, texture, and fine details replicates the in-store experience and reduces return rates by building confidence."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":3,"name":"Product video shows the item being used, unboxed, or worn","text":"Product pages without video miss out on up to 80% higher conversion rates. Video conveys size, movement, and quality in ways static images simply cannot."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":4,"name":"Price is large and shows savings with crossed-out original + percent off","text":"Without visible price anchoring, your discount feels invisible. Price anchoring triggers loss aversion — one of the strongest buying levers."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":5,"name":"'Add to Cart' is the most dominant element above the fold","text":"If your Add to Cart button doesn't visually dominate the page, shoppers literally don't see it — especially on mobile. A buried ATC button can silently cost you 15%+ of potential adds."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":6,"name":"Description opens with customer benefits before listing specs","text":"Feature-first descriptions bore shoppers and kill conversions. Nobody cares about '100% organic cotton' until they know why it matters to them. Benefits-first copy can lift conversions 20%+."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":7,"name":"Size guide pops up in-context without leaving the product page","text":"Sizing uncertainty causes 40% of apparel returns. An accessible, in-page size chart reduces returns and boosts purchase confidence."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":8,"name":"Variant selectors show real-time stock: 'Only 2 left in Medium'","text":"Scarcity paired with specificity creates urgency without feeling manipulative. Shoppers act faster when they see limited availability on their size."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":9,"name":"Estimated delivery date is shown, not just 'ships in 3-5 days'","text":"A concrete date ('Arrives by Friday, April 3') is 2x more motivating than vague ranges. It helps shoppers justify impulse and gift purchases."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":10,"name":"Customer reviews with star ratings, photos, and verified badges","text":"95% of shoppers read reviews before purchasing. Without them, you're asking people to trust you blindly. Photo reviews are 5x more influential because they show the product in real hands."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":11,"name":"Q&A section for product-specific questions and answers","text":"Unanswered questions kill conversions. A visible Q&A section lets future shoppers benefit from past answers, reducing support load and friction."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":12,"name":"'Frequently bought together' shows complementary products","text":"Relevant cross-sells increase AOV by 10–30%. One-click bundles make it effortless for shoppers to complete their purchase."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":13,"name":"Return/exchange policy summarized directly on the product page","text":"A visible, generous return policy lifts conversions by 17% on average. It removes the #1 fear of buying online: 'What if it doesn't work out?'"},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":14,"name":"Back-in-stock alerts for sold-out variants","text":"Capturing emails on sold-out items recovers otherwise lost revenue. These alerts have 10–15% conversion rates — far above typical email campaigns."}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Cart & Mini-Cart (9 checks)","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":1,"name":"Slide-out mini-cart confirms item added with thumbnail and details","text":"Keeping shoppers on the page (instead of redirecting to a cart page) encourages continued browsing and multiple product adds per session."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":2,"name":"Cart shows image, name, variant, unit price, quantity, and line total","text":"Full visibility prevents 'sticker shock' at checkout. When shoppers feel in control of their order, they're less likely to abandon."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":3,"name":"Quantity adjustment uses +/- buttons, not a dropdown","text":"Tap-friendly +/- buttons reduce friction on mobile. Dropdowns require precision tapping and extra steps — costing you impulse quantity increases."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":4,"name":"Free shipping progress bar shows how much more to spend to qualify","text":"Without a progress bar, shoppers have no reason to add more. With one, they spend 15–20% more just to earn free shipping. It's one of the highest-ROI elements you can add."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":5,"name":"In-cart upsell suggests a complementary product or upgrade","text":"A well-placed, relevant suggestion lifts AOV without feeling pushy. Keep it to 1–2 items max."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":6,"name":"Discount code field is collapsed, not prominently displayed","text":"A visible coupon field sends 27% of shoppers to Google for codes — and many never come back. Collapsing it keeps checkout-ready shoppers focused."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":7,"name":"Estimated tax, shipping, and total shown before clicking 'Checkout'","text":"48% of cart abandonment happens because of unexpected costs. Showing tax + shipping early is the single biggest cart abandonment fix."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":8,"name":"Cart persists for 7+ days via cookies or account","text":"Shoppers often research across devices and sessions. Persistent carts ensure they don't have to re-add products, recovering multi-session purchases."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":9,"name":"Cart shows a delivery estimate for the items in the order","text":"Showing 'Arrives by Thursday' inside the cart reinforces purchase intent and reduces last-minute hesitation before checkout."}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Checkout Flow (13 checks)","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":1,"name":"Guest checkout is the default — no forced account creation","text":"Forcing account creation before purchase kills 26% of checkouts — it's the #2 abandonment reason after price. Every day you require sign-up, you're turning away 1 in 4 ready-to-buy shoppers."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":2,"name":"Single-page checkout or clear step indicator","text":"Each extra checkout step bleeds 10–15% of your shoppers. A 4-step checkout loses up to 45% more people than a single-page one."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":3,"name":"Address fields auto-complete via Google Places or postal lookup","text":"Auto-fill reduces form completion time by 30% and eliminates typos that cause failed deliveries — a hidden source of returns and support tickets."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":4,"name":"Inline validation shows errors as the shopper types","text":"Post-submit error pages feel punishing and cause 20–40% of shoppers to give up. Real-time validation keeps the flow smooth and conversions high."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":5,"name":"Express checkout buttons (Shop Pay, Apple Pay, Google Pay) above the fold","text":"One-tap checkout eliminates form filling entirely. Stores enabling express checkout see 40–70% faster checkout times and measurably lower abandonment."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":6,"name":"Order summary with thumbnails visible at every checkout step","text":"Seeing product images during checkout reinforces the desire to own the items and prevents the 'what did I add again?' moment that causes drop-off."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":7,"name":"Shipping options show price, carrier, and estimated delivery date","text":"Clarity on shipping cost and speed lets shoppers make an informed choice. Ambiguity here causes 17% of checkout abandonments."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":8,"name":"Security badges and SSL lock near the credit card fields","text":"23% of shoppers abandon checkout because they don't feel safe entering their card. If there's no visible SSL lock or trust badge near your payment form, you're losing nearly 1 in 4 buyers."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":9,"name":"Discount code in checkout is collapsed or at the end","text":"Repeating the coupon field prominently at checkout re-triggers code-hunting behavior. Keeping it subtle retains shoppers who are ready to pay."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":10,"name":"Trust copy near 'Place Order': 'Secure checkout - Free returns'","text":"Last-second reassurance at the point of commitment can lift completion rates 5–10%. It addresses lingering doubts right when they matter most."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":11,"name":"Confirmation page shows order number, items, and delivery estimate","text":"A clear confirmation reduces 'did my order go through?' anxiety calls to support and sets accurate delivery expectations from the start."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":12,"name":"Confirmation email fires within 60 seconds with tracking link","text":"Instant confirmation emails have 65%+ open rates. Including a tracking link and product care tips starts the post-purchase relationship strong."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":13,"name":"Post-checkout optional account creation for faster future orders","text":"After the purchase, shoppers are receptive. Offering 'Save for faster checkout next time' converts 25–30% of guests into account holders."}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Trust & Social Proof (9 checks)","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":1,"name":"Display total review count or orders fulfilled on homepage","text":"Large aggregate numbers ('50,000+ 5-star reviews') create instant credibility. New visitors need proof that others trust your store before they will."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":2,"name":"Real customer photos (UGC) alongside reviews on product pages","text":"UGC photos are trusted 6x more than brand photos. They show real people using real products — the most powerful form of social proof."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":3,"name":"2–3 detailed testimonials on homepage or collection pages","text":"Specific, story-driven testimonials ('I was skeptical, but…') outperform star ratings alone because they address objections proactively."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":4,"name":"'As Seen In' logos from press or influencers if applicable","text":"Authority transfer is powerful. Logos from recognizable outlets signal that your brand has been vetted by trusted third parties."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":5,"name":"Trust badges on product pages and checkout","text":"Repetition of trust signals at multiple touchpoints compounds confidence. Showing badges on both product pages and checkout covers both stages of doubt."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":6,"name":"Video testimonials or unboxing videos from real customers","text":"Video testimonials feel more authentic and harder to fake. They convey genuine emotion and product quality better than text alone."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":7,"name":"Before/after photos for products where transformation matters","text":"Visual proof of results (skincare, fitness, home improvement) is the single most persuasive content for outcome-driven products."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":8,"name":"Professional 'About Us' page with brand story and team photos","text":"Shoppers buy from people, not faceless websites. A humanized About page builds emotional connection and differentiates you from dropshippers."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":9,"name":"Shipping and return policies easy to find from any page","text":"Hard-to-find policies signal something to hide. Easy access (footer + product page + FAQ) builds trust and reduces pre-purchase anxiety."}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Mobile Optimization (10 checks)","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":1,"name":"Sticky 'Add to Cart' bar when scrolling past the main button","text":"On long mobile product pages, the original ATC button scrolls away. A sticky bar keeps the purchase action always one tap away."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":2,"name":"All tap targets at least 44×44px with adequate spacing","text":"Tiny buttons on mobile cause mis-taps that send people to the wrong page, breaking their flow. If your buttons are under 44px, you're creating friction on every single tap."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":3,"name":"Checkout uses correct mobile input types (numeric, email keyboards)","text":"Showing the right keyboard (number pad for zip codes, @ keyboard for email) speeds up form entry and reduces typos on small screens."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":4,"name":"Product images served in WebP/AVIF with lazy loading","text":"Modern formats cut image file size 25–35% with no quality loss. Faster-loading product images directly correlate with higher mobile conversions."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":5,"name":"Body font at least 16px to prevent iOS auto-zoom on inputs","text":"iOS auto-zooms on any input field with font below 16px, breaking the mobile layout. This simple CSS fix eliminates a major UX annoyance."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":6,"name":"Mobile gallery supports swipe gestures between product photos","text":"Swiping is the most natural mobile interaction. Tap-only galleries feel clunky and discourage shoppers from viewing all product angles."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":7,"name":"Thumb-friendly filter/sort UI on collection pages","text":"Tiny desktop-style dropdowns are nearly unusable on mobile. Bottom sheets or slide-out filter panels let shoppers refine products easily."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":8,"name":"No horizontal scroll on any page","text":"Horizontal overflow breaks the mobile experience and looks unprofessional. It signals a store that doesn't care about mobile shoppers."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":9,"name":"Mobile PageSpeed score 75+ on homepage and top product pages","text":"Below 75 on PageSpeed, Google actively deprioritizes your store in search results AND shoppers leave before the page finishes loading. You're losing traffic and conversions simultaneously."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":10,"name":"Checkout CTA buttons placed in the thumb zone (bottom of screen)","text":"The bottom third of the screen is the easiest area to reach with one thumb. Placing 'Place Order' here reduces checkout friction on mobile."}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Site Search & Navigation (7 checks)","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":1,"name":"Search autocomplete with product names, images, and prices","text":"Rich search suggestions convert browsers into buyers by showing the exact product before they even finish typing. Visual results drive 30%+ higher CTR."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":2,"name":"Search handles typos, synonyms, and plurals gracefully","text":"A shopper typing a misspelling who gets zero results will leave. Fuzzy matching and synonym support ensures they always find what they're looking for."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":3,"name":"Zero-results page suggests popular products or categories","text":"A dead-end 'no results' page loses the shopper entirely. Offering alternatives keeps them browsing and salvages the session."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":4,"name":"Collection pages have intuitive filters: price, size, color, rating","text":"Filters help shoppers narrow large catalogs quickly. Without them, shoppers overwhelmed by choice leave without purchasing."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":5,"name":"Sort options: best-selling, price, newest, top-rated","text":"Different shoppers have different intent. Budget shoppers sort by price; trend-seekers sort by newest. Offering both captures more purchase intent."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":6,"name":"Mega menus with subcategories and a featured product image","text":"For stores with 50+ products, mega menus with visual cues help shoppers navigate directly to the right subcategory — reducing clicks to purchase."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":7,"name":"'Recently viewed' products on collection pages and homepage","text":"Shoppers often return to compare. Surfacing recently viewed products saves them from re-searching and increases return-visit conversion."}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Email & Retention (9 checks)","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":1,"name":"Abandoned cart series (3 emails at 1h, 24h, 72h) with product images","text":"Abandoned cart emails recover 5–15% of lost revenue. Three-touch sequences outperform single emails because shoppers need different nudges at different stages."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":2,"name":"Welcome series (3–5 emails over 7 days) introducing brand + best sellers","text":"New subscribers who don't receive a welcome series spend 33% less than those who do. Skipping this means leaving your highest-intent audience cold."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":3,"name":"Post-purchase review request 7–14 days after delivery","text":"Timing matters: asking too early (before arrival) annoys; too late, and the excitement fades. 7–14 days maximizes review collection rates."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":4,"name":"Win-back campaign for customers inactive 60–90 days","text":"Reactivating existing customers costs 5x less than acquiring new ones. A personalized 'We miss you' offer with a discount reignites purchase behavior."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":5,"name":"Browse abandonment email for products viewed 2+ times","text":"If a shopper viewed a product multiple times without adding to cart, they're interested but hesitant. A targeted email addressing common objections can tip them over."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":6,"name":"Transactional emails are branded with product recommendations","text":"Order confirmation emails have 70%+ open rates — the highest of any email type. Adding 'You might also like' recommendations turns logistics into revenue."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":7,"name":"Back-in-stock notifications for sold-out variants","text":"These automated alerts have 10–15% conversion rates — 5x higher than promotional emails. Shoppers who signed up already demonstrated high purchase intent."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":8,"name":"Post-delivery email asks for UGC in exchange for a reward","text":"Customer photos and unboxing videos are your most powerful marketing assets. A small loyalty reward incentivizes UGC creation at the peak of excitement."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":9,"name":"Replenishment reminders for consumable products","text":"Perfectly timed 'time to reorder' emails based on usage cycles drive predictable repeat revenue and reduce the chance of shoppers switching to competitors."}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Page Speed & Technical SEO (9 checks)","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":1,"name":"Core Web Vitals pass: LCP < 2.5s, INP < 200ms, CLS < 0.1","text":"Google uses Core Web Vitals as a ranking signal. Failing them means your store ranks lower AND your shoppers leave due to sluggish pages — a double hit."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":2,"name":"Product images lazy-load below the fold; hero images load eagerly","text":"Lazy loading defers off-screen images, cutting initial page load by 30–50%. Eager-loading hero images ensures the first impression is instant."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":3,"name":"Critical CSS inlined for product pages; rest loads async","text":"Inlining the CSS needed for above-the-fold content eliminates render-blocking requests, making the product page feel instant even on slow connections."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":4,"name":"Third-party scripts audited quarterly to remove slow ones","text":"Review widgets, chat tools, and tracking pixels can add 2–5 seconds of load time. Regular audits ensure only ROI-positive scripts remain."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":5,"name":"CDN serves product images from edge locations near your shoppers","text":"A CDN can cut image delivery time by 50%+ by serving files from servers closest to each shopper's location. Essential for international stores."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":6,"name":"Unique meta titles and descriptions on all product pages","text":"Duplicate or missing meta tags cause products to compete with each other in search results. Unique, keyword-rich tags drive organic product page traffic."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":7,"name":"Product schema structured data for rich search results","text":"Product ratings, price, and availability enable star ratings in Google results. Rich snippets increase organic CTR by 20–30% versus plain listings."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":8,"name":"Canonical URLs prevent duplicate indexing from filters/variants","text":"Filter combinations and variant URLs can create thousands of duplicate pages. Canonical tags consolidate SEO authority to your main product URLs."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":9,"name":"404 page shows search bar and links to popular products","text":"A helpful 404 page saves sessions that would otherwise bounce. Showing best sellers or a search bar redirects lost traffic back into the funnel."}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Analytics & Testing (8 checks)","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":1,"name":"GA4 e-commerce events: view_item, add_to_cart, begin_checkout, purchase","text":"Without proper event tracking, you're flying blind. These four events map the full purchase funnel and reveal exactly where shoppers drop off."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":2,"name":"Enhanced e-commerce funnel tracks each checkout step","text":"Without funnel tracking, you're guessing where shoppers leave. Is it shipping costs? Payment form? You don't know — and the fix for each is completely different."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":3,"name":"Heatmaps and session recordings on top 5 product pages","text":"Heatmaps reveal what shoppers actually look at (and ignore). Session recordings expose rage clicks, confusion, and friction you'd never find in analytics alone."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":4,"name":"A/B testing at least 2 experiments per month","text":"Stores that don't test leave their conversion rate to chance. Just 2 tests/month with a modest 3–5% average win rate compounds to 2x your conversion rate within a year."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":5,"name":"Revenue per visitor (RPV) tracked as primary CRO metric","text":"Conversion rate alone misses AOV changes. RPV captures both conversion and order value — the truest measure of optimization impact."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":6,"name":"Server-side tracking ensures events fire despite ad blockers","text":"Ad blockers prevent 15–30% of client-side tracking from firing. Server-side tracking captures these events so your data and retargeting stay accurate."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":7,"name":"Weekly CRO dashboard: conversion rate, AOV, cart abandonment, RPV","text":"A recurring dashboard creates accountability and surfaces trends early. Weekly review ensures you spot problems before they cost significant revenue."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":8,"name":"Add-to-cart rate tracked per product to find underperformers","text":"High-traffic, low-ATC products are your biggest opportunity. Improving their product page can unlock revenue that's already visiting your store."}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Copywriting & Persuasion (6 checks)","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":1,"name":"CTAs use first-person benefit copy: 'Get My 20% Off', not 'Submit'","text":"First-person CTAs outperform generic ones by 25–90%. They create psychological ownership before the shopper even clicks."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":2,"name":"Descriptions follow Problem → Agitation → Solution structure","text":"PAS copy framework hooks readers by naming their problem, amplifying it emotionally, then positioning your product as the solution. It outsells feature lists."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":3,"name":"Top 3–5 benefits bullet-pointed above the fold","text":"Scannable benefit bullets catch shoppers who won't read paragraphs. Placing them above the fold ensures they're seen before the shopper scrolls away."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":4,"name":"Urgency is honest: real deadlines, real stock — no fake timers","text":"Fake scarcity erodes trust and triggers refund requests. Honest urgency ('Sale ends Sunday at midnight') converts just as well without the backlash."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":5,"name":"Microcopy reduces anxiety: 'Free returns', 'Cancel anytime'","text":"Tiny reassurances near CTAs and form fields lower the perceived risk of taking action. They address micro-objections at the exact moment of hesitation."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":6,"name":"Collection headlines match shopper intent: 'Gifts Under $50'","text":"Intent-driven headlines put shoppers into the right frame of mind. 'Gifts Under $50' converts gift shoppers far better than 'Category: Budget'."}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","name":"Post-Purchase & Growth (5 checks)","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":1,"name":"Thank-you page offers referral discount: 'Give $10, Get $10'","text":"Post-purchase is the peak of customer excitement. A referral offer here converts 2–5x better than one buried in a follow-up email."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":2,"name":"Branded order tracking page with product recommendations","text":"Shoppers check tracking 3–5 times per order. A branded page with cross-sells turns logistics anxiety into a remarketing opportunity."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":3,"name":"Returns process is self-serve, clear, and in the confirmation email","text":"Easy returns increase lifetime value: 92% of shoppers say they'll buy again from a store with a hassle-free return process."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":4,"name":"Live chat or visible support contact on every page","text":"Pre-sale support converts hesitant browsers. A visible chat widget can lift conversions 10–15% by answering objections in real time."},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":5,"name":"Loyalty/rewards program with points per purchase and tier benefits","text":"Loyalty members spend 12–18% more per order and buy 33% more frequently. Points and tiers create switching costs that reduce churn to competitors."}]}]}</script><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"BreadcrumbList","itemListElement":[{"@